    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen `signcolumn` option is set to `yes` in $MYVIMRC, open hover floating window, the header divider line wraps at wrong position:\r\n![图片](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/45989017/c3d4e7b1-0385-4473-85ec-98d265787d93)\r\n\r\nThis also effects the diagnostic floating window:\r\n![图片](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/45989017/0491a9a8-8b1d-41f8-932e-47bee4faf144)\r\n\r\nSimilar issue: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12998\r\n\r\n### Workaround\r\n\r\nA workaround for this is to override the handler for `hover` and `signatureHelp` and turn off `signcolumn` option for the floating window. I think this should be solved in neovim itself for user-friendliness.\r\n```lua\r\nvim.lsp.handlers['textDocument/hover'] = vim.lsp.with(function(_, result, ctx, config)\r\n  local _, fwin = vim.lsp.handlers.hover(_, result, ctx, config)\r\n  if fwin then\r\n    vim.wo[fwin].signcolumn = 'no'\r\n  end\r\nend, { border = 'rounded' })\r\n\r\nvim.lsp.handlers['textDocument/signatureHelp'] = vim.lsp.with(function(_, result, ctx, config)\r\n  local _, fwin = vim.lsp.handlers.signature_help(_, result, ctx, config)\r\n  if fwin then\r\n    vim.wo[fwin].signcolumn = 'no'\r\n  end\r\nend, { border = 'rounded' })\r\n\r\n-- lsp on_attach mapping\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'gl', function()\r\n  local _, fwin = vim.diagnostic.open_float { scope = 'line' }\r\n  if fwin then\r\n    vim.wo[fwin].signcolumn = 'no'\r\n  end\r\nend, { desc = 'Show diagnostics', buffer = 0 })\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nFor hover floating window:\r\n![图片](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/45989017/4529fd9b-fc2e-4e4d-95a9-5cf9d6797207)\r\n\r\nFor diagnostic floating window:\r\n![图片](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/45989017/1709d9d7-0162-4a5a-9d76-bcc873f44914)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Language server name/version\r\n\r\nlua-language-server 3.6.23\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nDarwin Kernel Version 22.5.0\r\n\r\n### Log file\r\n\r\n_No response_",
